cs.NA, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.SC 

This paper deals with the numerical solution of partial differential equations using neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper uses fully connected multilayer perceptrons. The paper also discusses the use of cost functions and gradient descent, which are common in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper applies the method to boundary value problems, which falls under the category of scientific computing (cs.SC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of low-density grids, which could also be relevant to computational engineering (cs.CE).
